The government planned to borrow CZK 159.2 billion this year.
At the beginning of December, however, the ministry reduced the plan to CZK 152.8 billion due to better development of the state budget.
The state debt of the Czech Republic rose to CZK 842.7 billion at the end of September.
In the nine months of this year, it increased by CZK 40.2 billion.
Since June, however, it has decreased by CZK 13.4 billion.
The Ministry of Finance thus confirmed today its data on the state debt from the beginning of October.
Every Czech has a debt of over 84,000 crowns.
For the whole of last year, the state was indebted by more than 111 billion crowns.
"For the time being, it seems that thanks to the lower deficit for next year, we could not exceed the trillion crowns barrier until 2009.
