Better than expected
The 2007 State Debt Financing and Management Strategy shows that the government planned to borrow CZK 159.2 billion this year.
At the beginning of December, however, the ministry reduced the plan to CZK 152.8 billion due to better development of the state budget.
The amount consists mainly of the state budget deficit, which will probably reach CZK 76 billion this year instead of the expected CZK 91.3 billion.
It also includes the planned maximum resources for the Czech Consolidation Agency of CZK 13.3 billion, a ten-billion reserve for pension payments, financing of government bonds worth CZK 43 billion and repayments of loans from the European Investment Bank in the amount of CZK 1.8 billion.
