Serbs and Kosovo Albanians concluded their sixth and final round of talks in Baden, Austria, on Wednesday morning, without overcoming differences over the separatist province's future status.
"It is regrettable that the two sides were unable to reach a status agreement," European negotiator Wolfgang Ischinger said during a press conference in Vienna.
His American counterpart, Frank Wisner, stressed that peace in the region was "at stake" and appealed to Belgrade and Pristina to heed their commitments to keep the peace and be ready for dialogue even after the negotiations were over.
