The Americans and Europeans expect the talks to end on December 10.
Meanwhile, the Russians, who had previously blocked Kosovo's granting of independence in the UN Security Council, insist that negotiations continue beyond that deadline.
"Russia was and remains in favour of a negotiated solution, a compromise solution," Bocan-Kharchenko said.
