"For Serbia, only a solution from the Security Council is acceptable," Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica said.
"These negotiations lasted two years.
It must end as it began: in the Security Council."
Fatmir Sedjiu told reporters that "Kosovo's parliament will have the final say on status," adding that if there was a unilateral declaration of independence by the Albanian-speaking population, it would be "in agreement" with the West.
