The chief executive justified the offer to the former minister by saying that in political life "it is important to count on the best" and Bono "is among the best".
He further noted that "yes, it seems" that the politician from La Mancha will be the Socialist Party's candidate for President of Congress if the Socialists win the next election.
Bono would replace Manuel Marín, who on November 15 announced his decision not to run in the next general election and to abandon his active political career to devote himself to fighting climate change in university education.
