He went on to say that just as citizens know who the deputy economy minister will be if the PSOE wins the election, his party wanted to announce in a "transparent way" who would preside over Congress.
If Bono wins the job, he hopes to transform the House into "a house of respect, not insults or shouting" and making it "more and more like a citizen."
"Unfortunately, it sometimes seems that the only place in Madrid where it is not possible to speak in peace and quiet is Congress, the Prime Minister in the Senate has been interrupted 26 times on one occasion."
He also spoke highly of the current president, Manuel Marín, and "his good work" and did not want to put himself in his place for the time being, lest he stoop to what his opponents might consider "megalomania."
