Prosecutor of the Balkans
For eight years, Carla del Ponte has been mercilessly pursuing Balkan war criminals from the Public Prosecutor's Office of the Court of Justice in The Hague.
Her mandate expires at the end of the year, and Carla will leave with mixed feelings, as the main culprits of the Srebrenica massacre that killed 8,000 Bosnian Muslims, former General Ratko Mladic and former Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic, are still at large.
Their names are on the list from which Swiss director Marcel Schüpbach's documentary "Karla's List" (2006, not shown in Spain) takes its name, which, in the pace of a detective thriller, follows the work of the Swiss prosecutor in pursuing escaped criminals and pressuring the relevant states to pull the net.
Which insurance is right for me?
Car insurance to protect the driver in the event of an accident. It represents a considerable expense which depends on various factors such as age, status, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, it is necessary to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured person.
This commitment takes the form of an insurance contract, which provides that the insurance company receives an agreed sum insured in a certain amount in return for taking charge of paying damages in the event of an insured event.
Insurance premiums are the price of insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors such as age, status, gender, length of time to hold a driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the greater the likelihood of an accident occurring, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, based on inspections, insurance companies concluded that married people had fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way a vehicle is used will affect the frequency of journeys and therefore the likelihood that it will have an accident.
As the frequency of trips increases, the probability increases.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the price of premiums.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that best fits his profile as an insured person.
We will show you the most important variables for choosing this or that type of insurance, which, in addition to meeting the type of policyholder, will also be reasonably priced.
People under the age of twenty-five encounter various disadvantages, such as little driving experience and short holding of a driver's license when they want to buy insurance premiums at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks with a discount on premiums so as to get insurance coverage for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would assume the client's participation in the payment of the insured event.
"The part of the claim provided by the customer will be determined in advance when setting the premium price, which will be all the higher the lower the deductible", explains Luis Noguera, Chief Executive of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance broker.
Another option is insurance extended to other road users so that the client insures himself against damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendation.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be attentive and avoid crashes as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce premiums in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the base rate that an insurance company has.
On the other hand, malus is an increase in the basic rate.
"The bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus," Noguera explains.
After exceeding the twenty-five age mark, drivers have it easier when they go to take out insurance, because the client's risk index decreases, thanks to the experience they have gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to arrange insurance against all risks at a discount.
"Young people usually cannot benefit from the experience gained in advance when an accident occurs, nor when driving," assures the director of a European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when the "fear of the newcomer" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies to be the clients with the lowest risk index and therefore their surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a discount premium (which could amount to 300 euros) or at a high bonus, insurance extended to other road users, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their driving is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount," says Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to take out insurance against all risks with a premium discount (€150) or to cover other road users if a high bonus has been achieved.
It has to be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it protects drivers in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a good reason to study the insurance options that would suit us best in view of our personal circumstances.
